<TITLE> Rajshahi police list 54 Shibir men for RU incidents </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rajshahi, Feb 15 (bdnews24.com)  Rajshahi police have sent emergency bulletins to all districts with a list of 54 Islami Chhatra Shibir activists accused of last week's Rajshahi University violence and student killing. The messages were faxed Sunday night to all district police chiefs. Faruk Hossain, a Bangladesh Chhatra League activist, was killed and scores of students were injured during the fierce overnight clashes on Feb 8-9 between the activists of Chhatra League and Shibir. Rajshahi Metropolitan Police commissioner Nawsher Ali said that they had confirmed from the statements of Shibir activists, rounded up in mass arrests over the past week, that these 54 Shibir men were directly involved with the violence. "We have also made another list of those who were indirectly involved with the incident," he said. The Shibir men, including RU Shibir president Shamsul Alam Golap and general secretary Mobarak Hossain, have been named in cases filed in connection with the campus violence, killing of Faruk Hossain and attacks on several BCL activists that including cutting the tendons of their limbs. bdn
